shutdown the vm
Extend the physical disk
on the system
# lsblk
sda      8:0    0   40G  0 disk
├─sda1   8:1    0  600M  0 part /boot
└─sda2   8:2    0   20G  0 part /

###Resize the partition with parted
sudo parted /dev/sda
Inside the prompt:

(parted) print

##You’ll see something like:

Number  Start   End     Size    Type     File system  Flags
 1      1MB     600MB   600MB   primary  xfs          boot
 2      600MB   20GB    19.4GB  primary  xfs
Now extend partition 2 to the end of the disk:

(parted) resizepart 2 100%
(parted) quit

###
If your root is xfs (default in Fedora):

sudo xfs_growfs /


If your root is ext4:

sudo resize2fs /dev/sda2
